1. Open your PowerPoint presentation.
2. Press Alt + F11 to open the VBA editor.
3. In the VBA editor, insert a new module by right-clicking on any item in the project explorer, selecting Insert, and then choosing Module.
4. Copy and paste the VBA code into the module.
5. Modify the file path in the line ppt.Presentations.Open "C:\Path\To\Your\Presentation.pptx" to point to your actual presentation file.
6. Run the macro by pressing F5 or selecting Run from the menu.
